name: The Bad in Every Man
comments: The song was originally titled "Prayer", and written for Jean Harlow to sing in the movie "Hollywood Party".  However, it was never used in this movie.  The lyrics were then rewritten for the movie "Manhattan Melodrama" where it was sung by Shirley Ross.  Finally, the lyrics were again rewritten and the song released as the famous pop song "Blue Moon" in 1935.

comments: "Mbube" is Zulu for "lion".  The whole story of the song has been described by Rian Malan in "Where Does the Lion Sleep Tonight?".

name: Wimoweh
comments: Pete Seeger of The Weavers copied "Mbube" note for note, but he didn't understand "Uyimbube, uyimbube", so he made "Wimoweh" of it. At this stage the song is credited to Paul Campbell but this person is purely ficticious. For more information read "Where Does the Lion Sleep Tonight?" by Rian Malan.
